I like people who understand me well, but I hate those who understand me too well.
There is a part of me which I just want to be mine; my own little wooden secret box which I dare not open. And then some people just take this box away and break it open in front me. Why! It wasn't even your business!
Please stop it.
Also, die.

Enter at your own risk.

Prateekshit Pandey
I used to carry my feelings loose, like a professor with his books between classes.
"I carry the books loose for convenience, you see", I would often say, as I would wipe and polish each book cover. The title looks clearer when polished, and I would rearrange the books to put their titles in front.
I still carry them loose. And they still think it's for convenience.

Prateekshit Pandey
I never understood the long running human fantasy of flying.
What will you get by flying? A sense of thrill? The sheer amount of dirty, oxygen-less air pushing against you as you flap your wings? Or the cliched 'sense of freedom'? Seriously, that's what you'll do with your freedom?
Fly?
Tell that to the bird which is shitting on your window sill right now.
Try fantasizing lucid dreaming. That shit is dope.
‪#latenightthoughts‬

Taneea S Agrawaal
Remember how in love we were?
As if it wasn't just a feeling we shared deep down in bottom of our hearts, but rather a light, that shone bright. But that light soon went from feeling like a warm blanket over us in the winter to being absolutely cruel and piercing our skin with a thousand prickling needles like in the Indian summer.
It caused an explosion so powerful that now we are blinded as we stand in the midst of this universe that resulted because our love failed. We can't even look each...

Prateekshit Pandey
Remember how we were just water, and we came together to form blood. We imploded into a heart and we beat each day as we explored the path of love. But we went out of sync, and it went from symphony to dubstep to absolute crass cacophony; we couldn't carry it any longer. The heart exploded and now there is blood on our faces, as we stand as the living memorial of our love. We can't even look each other in the eye.
Because tombstones never face each other.

Prateekshit Pandey
Don't we all feel more secure when we are sad.
We often live our happy moments with a prevalent fear of losing it. But when we are sad, we know things are downhill, and the worse that can happen is it'll go a little south, but still remain downhill.
It's addictive, at times. And it scares me.

Prateekshit Pandey
Sometimes I feel like a sock.
Like a sock piled with other socks on sale in a supermarket, and people crowded around my lot, tearing each other off to get the right sock. The worst part is that if I land in someone's basket with other groceries, I feel good about myself. As if I am not worthless anymore. And I easily forget that I am supposed to be worn by someone, very soon.
Life stinks. And now it all makes sense.

Oh, but I can change channels.
